---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

export const prerender = true;
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Use"
  description="Terms and conditions for using SiliconFeed at siliconfeed.online."
  ogType="website"
  canonicalUrl="https://siliconfeed.online/terms"
>
  <article class="glass static-page static-page--boxed">
    <h1 class="static-page__title">Terms of Use</h1>
    <p class="static-page__p static-page__legal-note">
      Effective date: April 8, 2026. These terms govern your use of <strong>siliconfeed.online</strong> (“Site”) operated
      by SiliconFeed (“we”, “us”). They are a practical template for publishers and tools such as Google Publisher
      Center; they are <strong>not</strong> legal advice—have qualified counsel adapt them for your jurisdiction and
      products.
    </p>

    <h2 class="static-page__h2">Agreement</h2>
    <p class="static-page__p">
      By accessing or using the Site, you agree to these Terms of Use and our
      <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>. If you do not agree, do not use the Site.
    </p>

    <h2 class="static-page__h2">The service</h2>
    <p class="static-page__p">
      SiliconFeed provides news and editorial-style content about technology and related topics. Content is provided
      for general information and may be produced or assisted by automated systems with human oversight where we apply
      it. We may change, suspend, or discontinue any part of the Site at any time.
    </p>

    <h2 class="static-page__h2">Acceptable use</h2>
    <ul class="static-page__list">
      <li>Do not use the Site in any way that violates applicable law or third-party rights.</li>
      <li>Do not attempt to disrupt, overload, scrape, or probe the Site or our systems beyond normal browsing, RSS, or
        search-engine indexing as permitted by robots rules.</li>
      <li>Do not misrepresent your affiliation with SiliconFeed or use our branding in a misleading way.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="static-page__h2">Intellectual property</h2>
    <p class="static-page__p">
      The Site’s design, branding, original text we own, and compilation of content are protected by intellectual
      property laws where applicable. You may link to our pages and use short quotations for commentary; otherwise,
      reproduction requires our prior written permission unless allowed by law (e.g. fair use). Third-party names and
      marks belong to their owners.
    </p>

    <h2 class="static-page__h2">Disclaimer of warranties</h2>
    <p class="static-page__p">
      The Site and all content are provided <strong>“as is”</strong> and <strong>“as available”</strong>. We do not
      warrant that the Site will be uninterrupted, error-free, or free of harmful components. Content is not professional
      advice (legal, financial, medical, or otherwise). Always verify important facts with primary sources.
    </p>

    <h2 class="static-page__h2">Limitation of liability</h2>
    <p class="static-page__p">
      To the fullest extent permitted by law, SiliconFeed and its operators will not be liable for any indirect,
      incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, or any loss of profits, data, or goodwill, arising from
      your use of the Site. Our aggregate liability for any claim relating to the Site shall not exceed the greater of
      (a) one hundred U.S. dollars (USD $100) or (b) amounts you paid us specifically for the service giving rise to the
      claim in the twelve months before the claim (if any).
    </p>

    <h2 class="static-page__h2">Third-party links and services</h2>
    <p class="static-page__p">
      The Site may link to third-party websites, embeds, or services (including advertising or subscription tools). We do
      not control them; their terms and privacy practices apply. See our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> for how
      we handle data on the Site.
    </p>

    <h2 class="static-page__h2">Indemnity</h2>
    <p class="static-page__p">
      You agree to defend and indemnify SiliconFeed against claims, damages, and expenses (including reasonable
      attorneys’ fees) arising from your misuse of the Site or violation of these terms, to the extent permitted by
      law.
    </p>

    <h2 class="static-page__h2">Governing law and disputes</h2>
    <p class="static-page__p">
      These terms are governed by the laws of the United States and the State of Delaware, without regard to conflict-of-law
      rules, except where mandatory consumer protections in your country apply. Courts in Delaware (or another venue we
      specify in an update) shall have exclusive jurisdiction for disputes, unless the law where you live requires
      otherwise—<strong>update this section with your lawyer for your actual entity and location.</strong>
    </p>

    <h2 class="static-page__h2">Changes</h2>
    <p class="static-page__p">
      We may update these terms by posting a new version on this page and changing the effective date. Continued use
      after changes constitutes acceptance where the law allows.
    </p>

    <h2 class="static-page__h2">Contact</h2>
    <p class="static-page__p">
      Questions about these terms:
      <a href="mailto:hello@siliconfeed.online">hello@siliconfeed.online</a>.
    </p>
